16/03/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The new parliament is to meet Monday (17 March) to discuss the composition of the council of ministers, according to Dragoljub Micunovic, chairman of the legislature. During the session, Serbian-Montenegrin President Svetozar Marovic, who also serves as prime minister, will unveil his choice for cabinet members. The parliament session had been scheduled for last Thursday, but was postponed after the assassination of Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Djindjic. (Tanjug, BBC - 14/03/03)
